        "sha": "7062d9fae1803a1bdfe70cf5a994e5dfaac792bb",
        "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/trees/7062d9fae1803a1bdfe70cf5a994e5dfaac792bb"
      },
      "verification": {
        "verified": true,
        "reason": "valid",
        "payload": "tree 7062d9fae1803a1bdfe70cf5a994e5dfaac792bb\nparent 672eedc46b064a3349b943b842362102c213fe95\nauthor Pol Espinasa <pol.espinasa@uab.cat> 1782916959 +0200\ncommitter Pol Espinasa <pol.espinasa@uab.cat> 1782917814 +0200\n\nwallet: avoid call bumpfeediscount with negative values\n\nChooseSelectionResult computes the bump-fee discount as: summed_bump_fees - combined_bump_fee\nWhere summed_bump_fees is the sum of per-UTXO ancestor bump fees and combined_bump_fee is the\ntrue combined cost taking into account shared ancestors.\n\nBoth variables use creates a fresh MiniMiner snapshot of the mempool. Because of that\nthe two snapshots of the mempool might be different. An artificial feerate decrease\nof an ancestor using prioritizesettransaction can make combined_bump_fee > summed_bump_fees.\nThis cause calling bumpfeediscount with a negative vaule triggering an assertion >= 0.\n\nThis commit fixes this by only calling bumpfeediscount when the discount is strictly positive.\n\nCo-authored-by: dergoegge <n.goeggi@gmail.com>\n",
        "signature": "-----BEGIN PGP SIGNATURE-----\n\niIsEABYKADMWIQRd8IHT46QaaYw3spsoRwkHtAvybQUCakUq1BUccG9sLmVzcGlu\nYXNhQHVhYi5jYXQACgkQKEcJB7QL8m3UIAEAzKu41aqlSQ60V8QwExY2aQE3qTnW\nvTeI8f8oYQ2Zb+kBAMPqpauLfwbQpuP9nxmJG3mlbxrFBIOFxXIBY4IRDQMP\n=ZfcB\n-----END PGP SIGNATURE-----"
      },
      "parents": [
        {
          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/672eedc46b064a3349b943b842362102c213fe95",
          "sha": "672eedc46b064a3349b943b842362102c213fe95",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/672eedc46b064a3349b943b842362102c213fe95"
        }
      ],
      "message": "wallet: avoid call bumpfeediscount with negative values\n\nChooseSelectionResult computes the bump-fee discount as: summed_bump_fees - combined_bump_fee\nWhere summed_bump_fees is the sum of per-UTXO ancestor bump fees and combined_bump_fee is the\ntrue combined cost taking into account shared ancestors.\n\nBoth variables use creates a fresh MiniMiner snapshot of the mempool. Because of that\nthe two snapshots of the mempool might be different. An artificial feerate decrease\nof an ancestor using prioritizesettransaction can make combined_bump_fee > summed_bump_fees.\nThis cause calling bumpfeediscount with a negative vaule triggering an assertion >= 0.\n\nThis commit fixes this by only calling bumpfeediscount when the discount is strictly positive.\n\nCo-authored-by: dergoegge <n.goeggi@gmail.com>",
